# RAG2F Configuration via Environment Variables

## Overview
Environment variables follow the naming convention:
RAG2F__<SECTION>__<KEY>__<SUBKEY>...

Sections can be:
- RAG2F: Core RAG2F settings
- PLUGINS: Plugin-specific configurations

## RAG2F Core Settings

# Standard embedder to use
RAG2F__RAG2F__EMBEDDER_DEFAULT=azure_openai

# Logging level
RAG2F__RAG2F__LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# Maximum retries for operations
RAG2F__RAG2F__MAX_RETRIES=3

## Plugin Configurations

### Azure OpenAI Embedder Plugin
# Note: Plugin ID in env vars is uppercased: AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDER

# Azure endpoint URL
RAG2F__PLUGINS__AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDER__AZURE_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.openai.azure.com

# API key for authentication
RAG2F__PLUGINS__AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDER__API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# Azure OpenAI API version
RAG2F__PLUGINS__AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDER__API_VERSION=2024-02-15-preview

# Deployment name for the embedding model
RAG2F__PLUGINS__AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDER__DEPLOYMENT=text-embedding-ada-002

# Embedding vector dimension
RAG2F__PLUGINS__AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDER__SIZE=1536

# Request timeout in seconds (optional, default: 30.0)
RAG2F__PLUGINS__AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDER__TIMEOUT=30.0

# Maximum number of retries (optional, default: 2)
RAG2F__PLUGINS__AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDER__MAX_RETRIES=2

### Example: Another Plugin Configuration
# RAG2F__PLUGINS__ANOTHER_PLUGIN__SETTING1=value1
# RAG2F__PLUGINS__ANOTHER_PLUGIN__SETTING2=42

### Nested Configuration Example
# For nested structures in JSON, use additional separators:
# JSON: {"plugins": {"my_plugin": {"database": {"host": "localhost", "port": 5432}}}}
# ENV:  RAG2F__PLUGINS__MY_PLUGIN__DATABASE__HOST=localhost
# ENV:  RAG2F__PLUGINS__MY_PLUGIN__DATABASE__PORT=5432

## Type Inference
# Environment variable values are parsed as JSON first, then fall back to strings:
# - Numbers: RAG2F__PLUGINS__MY_PLUGIN__PORT=5432 → 5432 (integer)
# - Booleans: RAG2F__PLUGINS__MY_PLUGIN__ENABLED=true → true (boolean)
# - Arrays: RAG2F__PLUGINS__MY_PLUGIN__TAGS='["tag1","tag2"]' → ["tag1", "tag2"]
# - Objects: RAG2F__PLUGINS__MY_PLUGIN__META='{"key":"value"}' → {"key": "value"}
# - Strings: RAG2F__PLUGINS__MY_PLUGIN__NAME=MyPlugin → "MyPlugin"

## Priority
# Environment variables have HIGHER priority than JSON configuration.
# If both are provided, env vars will override JSON values.

